title: Amazon API Gateway
description:
Amazon API Gateway Amazon API Gateway helps developers deliver robust, secure,
and scalable mobile and web application back ends. API Gateway allows developers
to securely connect mobile and web applications to APIs that run on AWS Lambda,
Amazon EC2, or other publicly addressable web services that are hosted outside
of AWS.

GetAccount.title: GetAccount
GetAccount.description: Gets information about the current Account resource.

UpdateAccount.title: UpdateAccount
UpdateAccount.description: Changes information about the current Account resource.

GetApiKeys.title: GetApiKeys
GetApiKeys.description: Gets information about the current ApiKeys resource.

CreateApiKey.title: CreateApiKey
CreateApiKey.description:
Create an ApiKey resource. 

AWS CLI
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/apigateway/create-api-key.html]

ImportApiKeys.title: ImportApiKeys
ImportApiKeys.description: Import API keys from an external source, such as a CSV-formatted file.

GetApiKey.title: GetApiKey
GetApiKey.description: Gets information about the current ApiKey resource.

GetClientCertificate.title: GetClientCertificate
GetClientCertificate.description: Gets information about the current ClientCertificate resource.

GetDomainName.title: GetDomainName
GetDomainName.description: Represents a domain name that is contained in a simpler, more intuitive URL that can be called.

GetRestApis.title: GetRestApis
GetRestApis.description: Lists the RestApis resources for your collection.

ImportRestApi.title: ImportRestApi
ImportRestApi.description: A feature of the API Gateway control service for creating a new API from an external API definition file.

GetRestApi.title: GetRestApi
GetRestApi.description: Lists the RestApi resource in the collection.

PutRestApi.title: PutRestApi
PutRestApi.description: A feature of the API Gateway control service for updating an existing API with an input of external API definitions. The update can take the form of merging the supplied definition into the existing API or overwriting the existing API.

UpdateRestApi.title: UpdateRestApi
UpdateRestApi.description: Changes information about the specified API.

GetAuthorizers.title: GetAuthorizers
GetAuthorizers.description:
Describe an existing Authorizers resource.

AWS CLI
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/apigateway/get-authorizers.html]

CreateAuthorizer.title: CreateAuthorizer
CreateAuthorizer.description:
Adds a new Authorizer resource to an existing RestApi resource.

AWS CLI
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/apigateway/create-authorizer.html]

DeleteAuthorizer.title: DeleteAuthorizer
DeleteAuthorizer.description:
Deletes an existing Authorizer resource.

AWS CLI
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/apigateway/delete-authorizer.html]

GetAuthorizer.title: GetAuthorizer
GetAuthorizer.description:
Describe an existing Authorizer resource.

AWS CLI
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/apigateway/get-authorizer.html]

TestInvokeAuthorizer.title: TestInvokeAuthorizer
TestInvokeAuthorizer.description:
Simulate the execution of an Authorizer in your RestApi with headers,
parameters, and an incoming request body.

Enable custom authorizers
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/use-custom-authorizer.html]

UpdateAuthorizer.title: UpdateAuthorizer
UpdateAuthorizer.description:
Updates an existing Authorizer resource.

AWS CLI
[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/apigateway/update-authorizer.html]

CreateDeployment.title: CreateDeployment
CreateDeployment.description: Creates a Deployment resource, which makes a specified RestApi callable over the internet.

DeleteDeployment.title: DeleteDeployment
DeleteDeployment.description: Deletes a Deployment resource. Deleting a deployment will only succeed if there are no Stage resources associated with it.

GetGatewayResponses.title: GetGatewayResponses
GetGatewayResponses.description: Gets the GatewayResponses collection on the given RestApi. If an API developer has not added any definitions for gateway responses, the result will be the API Gateway-generated default GatewayResponses collection for the supported response types.

DeleteGatewayResponse.title: DeleteGatewayResponse
DeleteGatewayResponse.description: Clears any customization of a GatewayResponse of a specified response type on the given RestApi and resets it with the default settings.

GetGatewayResponse.title: GetGatewayResponse
GetGatewayResponse.description: Gets a GatewayResponse of a specified response type on the given RestApi.

PutGatewayResponse.title: PutGatewayResponse
PutGatewayResponse.description: Creates a customization of a GatewayResponse of a specified response type and status code on the given RestApi.

UpdateGatewayResponse.title: UpdateGatewayResponse
UpdateGatewayResponse.description: Updates a GatewayResponse of a specified response type on the given RestApi.

GetModels.title: GetModels
GetModels.description: Describes existing Models defined for a RestApi resource.

CreateModel.title: CreateModel
CreateModel.description: Adds a new Model resource to an existing RestApi resource.

GetModel.title: GetModel
GetModel.description: Describes an existing model defined for a RestApi resource.

GetModelTemplate.title: GetModelTemplate
GetModelTemplate.description: Generates a sample mapping template that can be used to transform a payload into the structure of a model.

GetRequestValidators.title: GetRequestValidators
GetRequestValidators.description: Gets the RequestValidators collection of a given RestApi.

GetResources.title: GetResources
GetResources.description: Lists information about a collection of Resource resources.

PutMethod.title: PutMethod
PutMethod.description: Add a method to an existing Resource resource.

TestInvokeMethod.title: TestInvokeMethod
TestInvokeMethod.description: Simulate the execution of a Method in your RestApi with headers, parameters, and an incoming request body.

PutMethodResponse.title: PutMethodResponse
PutMethodResponse.description: Adds a MethodResponse to an existing Method resource.

GetStages.title: GetStages
GetStages.description: Gets information about one or more Stage resources.

CreateStage.title: CreateStage
CreateStage.description: Creates a new Stage resource that references a pre-existing Deployment for the API.

FlushStageAuthorizersCache.title: FlushStageAuthorizersCache
FlushStageAuthorizersCache.description: Flushes all authorizer cache entries on a stage.

GetExport.title: GetExport
GetExport.description: Exports a deployed version of a RestApi in a specified format.

GetSdk.title: GetSdk
GetSdk.description: Generates a client SDK for a RestApi and Stage.

GetTags.title: GetTags
GetTags.description: Gets the Tags collection for a given resource.

TagResource.title: TagResource
TagResource.description: Adds or updates a tag on a given resource.

UntagResource.title: UntagResource
UntagResource.description: Removes a tag from a given resource.

GetUsagePlans.title: GetUsagePlans
GetUsagePlans.description: Gets all the usage plans of the caller's account.

CreateUsagePlan.title: CreateUsagePlan
CreateUsagePlan.description: Creates a usage plan with the throttle and quota limits, as well as the associated API stages, specified in the payload.

DeleteUsagePlan.title: DeleteUsagePlan
DeleteUsagePlan.description: Deletes a usage plan of a given plan Id.

GetUsagePlan.title: GetUsagePlan
GetUsagePlan.description: Gets a usage plan of a given plan identifier.

UpdateUsagePlan.title: UpdateUsagePlan
UpdateUsagePlan.description: Updates a usage plan of a given plan Id.

GetUsagePlanKeys.title: GetUsagePlanKeys
GetUsagePlanKeys.description: Gets all the usage plan keys representing the API keys added to a specified usage plan.

CreateUsagePlanKey.title: CreateUsagePlanKey
CreateUsagePlanKey.description: Creates a usage plan key for adding an existing API key to a usage plan.

DeleteUsagePlanKey.title: DeleteUsagePlanKey
DeleteUsagePlanKey.description: Deletes a usage plan key and remove the underlying API key from the associated usage plan.

GetUsagePlanKey.title: GetUsagePlanKey
GetUsagePlanKey.description: Gets a usage plan key of a given key identifier.

UpdateUsage.title: UpdateUsage
UpdateUsage.description: Grants a temporary extension to the remaining quota of a usage plan associated with a specified API key.

GetUsage.title: GetUsage
GetUsage.description: Gets the usage data of a usage plan in a specified time interval.

GetVpcLinks.title: GetVpcLinks
GetVpcLinks.description: Gets the VpcLinks collection under the caller's account in a selected region.

CreateVpcLink.title: CreateVpcLink
CreateVpcLink.description: Creates a VPC link, under the caller's account in a selected region, in an asynchronous operation that typically takes 2-4 minutes to complete and become operational. The caller must have permissions to create and update VPC Endpoint services.

DeleteVpcLink.title: DeleteVpcLink
DeleteVpcLink.description: Deletes an existing VpcLink of a specified identifier.

GetVpcLink.title: GetVpcLink
GetVpcLink.description: Gets a specified VPC link under the caller's account in a region.

UpdateVpcLink.title: UpdateVpcLink
UpdateVpcLink.description: Updates an existing VpcLink of a specified identifier.
